Congratulations!

76
00:07:53,040 --> 00:07:54,220
BTW,

77
00:07:54,220 --> 00:07:56,880
did you know that the /ɪr/ sound

78
00:07:56,880 --> 00:08:01,380
is represented by at least six combinations of letters?

79
00:08:01,380 --> 00:08:02,940
Take a look:

80
00:08:02,940 --> 00:08:07,240
'er' as in "here," or "zero,"

81
00:08:07,240 --> 00:08:12,040
'ear' as in "dear" or "fear,"

82
00:08:12,040 --> 00:08:16,980
'eer' as in "beer" or "deer."

83
00:08:16,980 --> 00:08:21,440
There are a few words with the 'ier' combination,

84
00:08:21,440 --> 00:08:25,200
as in "pier" or "cashier",

85
00:08:25,200 --> 00:08:28,880
'ir' as in "spirit"

86
00:08:28,880 --> 00:08:33,940
and 'irr', as in "mirror."

87
00:08:34,720 --> 00:08:40,960
While these combinations of letters represent the /ɪr/ sound in some words,

88
00:08:40,960 --> 00:08:46,040
they may also represent other R-colored vowels in other words.

89
00:08:46,040 --> 00:08:47,860
As we've said before,

90
00:08:47,860 --> 00:08:50,420
English spelling is never easy.

91
